---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Cloud Setup" description="Deploy Memlayer to the cloud with Supabase and Fly.io">
<main class="container" style="padding-top:48px;padding-bottom:60px;max-width:700px">
  <h1 style="font-size:32px">Cloud Setup</h1>
  <p style="color:var(--text-dim)">Deploy Memlayer to <strong>Supabase</strong> (database) + <strong>Fly.io</strong> (server) for a fully cloud-hosted stack. No Docker or VPS management needed.</p>

  <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:16px 20px;margin:24px 0">
    <strong>Cost:</strong> Free tier covers 1-10 users. Supabase Pro ($25/mo) + Fly.io (~$2/mo) scales to hundreds.
  </div>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul style="color:var(--text-dim);padding-left:20px;margin-bottom:24px">
    <li>A <a href="https://supabase.com">Supabase</a> account (free tier works)</li>
    <li>A <a href="https://fly.io">Fly.io</a> account with <strong>billing info added</strong> (free tier works, but Fly requires a credit card before deploying machines &mdash; add it at <a href="https://fly.io/dashboard">fly.io/dashboard</a> &rarr; Billing)</li>
    <li>The <code>flyctl</code> CLI installed and authenticated</li>
    <li>An OpenAI API key (optional, for vector embeddings)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>1. Create a Supabase Project</h2>
  <ol style="color:var(--text-dim);padding-left:20px;margin-bottom:24px">
    <li>Go to <a href="https://supabase.com/dashboard">supabase.com/dashboard</a> and create a new project</li>
    <li>Choose a region close to where you'll deploy Fly.io</li>
    <li>Set a strong database password (the setup script won't need it separately)</li>
    <li>Wait for the project to finish provisioning</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Enable Required Extensions</h3>
  <p>In your Supabase dashboard, go to <strong>Database → Extensions</strong> and enable:</p>
  <ul style="color:var(--text-dim);padding-left:20px;margin-bottom:24px">
    <li><code>vector</code> — pgvector for embedding similarity search</li>
    <li><code>pg_trgm</code> — trigram indexes for full-text search</li>
  </ul>
  <p style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:14px">Supabase installs these in its <code>extensions</code> schema rather than <code>public</code>. The Memlayer server detects this automatically &mdash; no extra configuration needed.</p>

  <h3>Get the Connection String</h3>
  <p>Go to <strong>Settings → Database → Connection string → URI</strong>.</p>
  <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:16px 20px;margin:16px 0">
    <strong>Important:</strong> Use the <strong>direct connection</strong> (port 5432), not the pooled connection (port 6543). Memlayer uses asyncpg with prepared statements, which requires a direct PostgreSQL connection.
  </div>

  <h2>2. Run the Setup Script</h2>
  <p>Clone the repo and run the cloud setup:</p>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/mikeydotio/memlayer.git
cd memlayer
./setup_cloud_hosted.sh</code></pre>
  <p>The script will:</p>
  <ul style="color:var(--text-dim);padding-left:20px;margin-bottom:24px">
    <li>Verify flyctl is installed and authenticated</li>
    <li>Prompt for your Supabase connection string</li>
    <li>Generate a secure auth token</li>
    <li>Optionally validate your OpenAI API key</li>
    <li>Deploy the server to Fly.io</li>
    <li>Wait for the health check to pass</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Install the Client</h2>
  <p>On each machine where you use Claude Code:</p>
  <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mikeydotio/memlayer/main/install.sh | bash</code></pre>
  <p>Then run the client setup with the server URL and auth token from the cloud setup output:</p>
  <pre><code>~/.memlayer/setup_client.sh --server-url https://YOUR-APP.fly.dev/api --auth-token YOUR_TOKEN</code></pre>
  <p>Or run <code>~/.memlayer/setup_client.sh</code> without arguments for an interactive setup.</p>

  <h2>Architecture</h2>
  <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:16px 20px;margin:16px 0;font-family:'SF Mono','Cascadia Code',monospace;font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
    Client (daemon + MCP)<br>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;↓ HTTPS<br>
    Fly.io (FastAPI server)<br>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;↓ Direct PostgreSQL<br>
    Supabase (pgvector database)
  </div>
  <ul style="color:var(--text-dim);padding-left:20px;margin-bottom:24px">
    <li><strong>Fly.io</strong> runs the FastAPI server with in-process embedding and eviction workers</li>
    <li><strong>Supabase</strong> hosts PostgreSQL with pgvector for hybrid search</li>
    <li>Response files are stored on a Fly.io persistent volume</li>
    <li>Fly machines scale to zero when idle and wake on request</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Managing Your Deployment</h2>
  <h3>View logs</h3>
  <pre><code>flyctl logs -a YOUR_APP_NAME</code></pre>

  <h3>Redeploy after updates</h3>
  <pre><code>cd memlayer
git pull
./deploy/fly-deploy.sh YOUR_APP_NAME</code></pre>

  <h3>Update secrets</h3>
  <pre><code>flyctl secrets set OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-... -a YOUR_APP_NAME</code></pre>

  <h3>Scale up</h3>
  <pre><code># Increase memory
flyctl scale memory 512 -a YOUR_APP_NAME

# Keep machine always running (no scale-to-zero)
flyctl scale count 1 -a YOUR_APP_NAME</code></pre>

  <h2>Re-running after failure</h2>
  <p>The setup script saves your configuration (auth token, database URL, app name) to <code>~/.config/memlayer/cloud.env</code>. If it fails at any step, just run it again &mdash; it will detect your saved config and offer to reuse it.</p>
  <pre><code># Re-run the full setup (reuses saved config)
./setup_cloud_hosted.sh

# Or retry just the deploy step
source ~/.config/memlayer/cloud.env
./deploy/fly-deploy.sh $MEMLAYER_APP_NAME</code></pre>
  <p>Common failure scenarios:</p>
  <ul style="color:var(--text-dim);padding-left:20px;margin-bottom:24px">
    <li><strong>Billing not set up</strong> &mdash; Add billing at <a href="https://fly.io/dashboard">fly.io/dashboard</a> &rarr; Billing, then re-run</li>
    <li><strong>Extensions not enabled</strong> &mdash; Enable <code>vector</code> and <code>pg_trgm</code> in Supabase, then re-run</li>
    <li><strong>Wrong connection string</strong> &mdash; Re-run and choose "no" when asked to keep the existing string</li>
    <li><strong>Deploy failed mid-build</strong> &mdash; Re-run (app/volume already exist and will be reused)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
  <h3>Health check fails</h3>
  <pre><code>flyctl logs -a YOUR_APP_NAME</code></pre>
  <p>Common causes: wrong connection string, extensions not enabled, or Supabase project paused (free tier pauses after 1 week of inactivity).</p>

  <h3>Prepared statement errors</h3>
  <p>You're using the pooled connection (port 6543) instead of direct (port 5432). Update the secret:</p>
  <pre><code>flyctl secrets set DATABASE_URL="postgresql://..." -a YOUR_APP_NAME</code></pre>

  <h3>Slow first request</h3>
  <p>Fly machines scale to zero after idle periods. The first request wakes the machine (~2-5 seconds). Set <code>min_machines_running = 1</code> in <code>fly.toml</code> to keep it always on (~$1.94/mo).</p>

  <h3>Supabase project paused</h3>
  <p>Free tier Supabase projects pause after 1 week of inactivity. Go to your dashboard and click "Restore" to unpause. Upgrade to Pro ($25/mo) to prevent pausing.</p>
</main>
</Base>
